![diagram](https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRwkHr_W2B2_TxIzQOYmWvvYFvak310zhq0x-Kjtp87VWTfbZdVLDoOZzB9YWvgPLLrw3M&amp;usqp=CAU)
:::

:::


Every second, the Sun fuses about `600 million tons of hydrogen` into helium, releasing energy equivalent to **billions of hydrogen bombs**.
</md></sn><sn><md>## Radiation{.text-center}

Only a fraction of the mass of hydrogen is converted into helium; the lost mass is transformed into energy according to **Einstein’s equation, E = mc²**.This is the source of all the Sun’s light and heat.

---

### Transport of Energy Inside the Sun

The energy created in the core must travel outward before it can escape into space:

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-lg-6
1. **Radiative Zone**

   * Energy moves slowly through radiation.
   * Photons (packets of light energy) are absorbed and re-emitted by particles.
   * It can take **thousands to millions of years** for a photon to pass through this zone.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-lg-6
2. **Convective Zone**

   * Energy moves by convection currents.
   * Hot plasma rises toward the surface, cools, then sinks back down.
   * This creates a constant boiling-like motion within the Sun.
:::

:::
